CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper June 2, 1962, pg. 1, reads: "One of the Surprises of the Friday meeting was the appearance of William Johnson of Stroudsburg, Pa. Mr. Johnson, an ardent Scranton booster, was former president of the Pennsylvania Junior Chamber of Commerce, the first Negro ever elected to this important office. - All Photos by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Gubernatorial candidate William "Bill" Scranton shaking hands with William Johnson with "Pennsylvania Needs Bill Scranton For Governor" sign in background, for Republican banquet at Loendi Club
